Parameters
usecMicroseconds timestamp
valueValue data
Returns
DB_NOERROR when successful, negative number on failure

◆ read_next() [1/4]

template<typename T >
dbstatus_t storage::types::TimeSeries< T >::read_next ( db_timestamp_usec_t &  timestamp_dest,
T &  value_dest 
)

Read next timestamp/value pair from series.

Parameters
[out]timestamp_destDestination for timestamp data
[out]value_destDestination for value data
Returns
number of timestamp/value pairs read when successful, negative number on failure

Reads the next timestamp/value pair from the series. Timestamps and values are sorted in ascending order by time.

If no timestamp/value pairs remain, DB_ENOMOREDATA is returned.

◆ read_next() [2/4]

template<typename T >
template<size_t N>
dbstatus_t storage::types::TimeSeries< T >::read_next ( db_timestamp_usec_t(&)  timestamp_dest[N],
T(&)  value_dest[N] 
)

Read next batch of timestamp/value pairs from series.

Parameters
[out]timestamp_destDestination for timestamp data
[out]value_destDestination for value data
Returns
number of timestamp/value pairs read when successful, negative number on failure

Reads up to N timestamp/value pairs from the series into the arrays timestamp_dest and value_dest. Timestamps and values are sorted in ascending order by time.

If no timestamp/value pairs remain, 0 is returned.
